race.comment: Maidens don't come a lot weaker than this which means WHAT A GENT (8) is a tremendous chance to open the account. Very good two back when beaten under a length over the mile at Dubbo in a Class 1. Went poorly at Wyong on Sunday but the five-day back-up is a good sign from the stable. Should be too good if on-song. NORTOKO (6) worked home well to finish second over 1300m at Narromine two back then went poorly at Warren last time. Hard one to follow but the addition of blinkers for the first time may have some effect. BROADCAST BOOGIE (3) returned her best figure at her only visit to Orange when edged out in a 1400m maiden on 9 October. Finding the line well and should enjoy getting to this distance for the first time. WEDDAMEENOOTZ (2) was left behind first-up at Hawkesbury but can do better in this easier race with the blinkers on. FLAMEON (5) isn't the most reliable conveyance but must go in the exotics.
